<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>be wide of the mark • come short of the mark</xh5><p> <i>be wide of the mark</i>—(also: be off the mark) be inaccurate or erroneous in one’s judgment: The idea that the Israelis are anxious to dictate a Carthaginian peace <u>is</u> ludicrously <u>wide of the mark</u>.</p><p> <i>come short of the mark</i>—(also: fall short of the mark) fail to attain some desired object or end: A perfectly good talk can be ruined if your answers to questions <u>come short of the mark</u>.</p> </entry>
